{"root":{"data":{"text":"Literature Review on Macrobrachium rosenbergii Research"},"children":[{"data":{"text":"I. Aquaculture Optimization & Growth Regulation"},"children":[{"data":{"text":"1. Photoperiod Regulation (Wang, 2025)"},"children":[{"data":{"text":"**Finding**: Extended photoperiod (L24:D0) promotes molting and enhances early growth performance (survival, weight gain) in juvenile prawns."},"children":[]},{"data":{"text":"**Evaluation**: Future studies should extend to other tissues (e.g., nervous system) to fully understand photoperiodic signaling."},"children":[]}]},{"data":{"text":"2. Feed Nutrition Innovation (Chen, 2025)"},"children":[{"data":{"text":"**Finding**: Defatted black soldier fly larvae meal (BSFLM) is a viable fishmeal substitute in prawn diets."},"children":[]},{"data":{"text":"**Evaluation**: Research needed on long-term effects, cost-effectiveness, and validation across farming models."},"children":[]}]}]},{"data":{"text":"II. Disease Control & Health Management"},"children":[{"data":{"text":"1. Bacterial Infection & Gut Health (Tang, 2025)"},"children":[{"data":{"text":"**Finding**: *Vibrio* infection causes intestinal dysbiosis, impairs barrier function, and damages tissue in prawns."},"children":[]},{"data":{"text":"**Evaluation**: Findings require validation across different farming models and geographical regions."},"children":[]}]},{"data":{"text":"2. Novel Antiviral Strategy (Chantunmapitak, 2025)"},"children":[{"data":{"text":"**Finding**: Engineered a novel antiviral strategy against *Macrobrachium rosenbergii* nodavirus (MrNV) based on viral capsid engineering and glycan recognition."},"children":[]},{"data":{"text":"**Evaluation**: Integrates structural biology and glycobiology, offering a new paradigm for antiviral design."},"children":[]}]},{"data":{"text":"3. Probiotic Application (Mahfuz, 2025)"},"children":[{"data":{"text":"**Finding**: Host-derived probiotics are a highly effective and species-specific alternative for sustainable prawn aquaculture."},"children":[]},{"data":{"text":"**Evaluation**: The specific biological mechanisms behind this effect require further in-depth exploration."},"children":[]}]},{"data":{"text":"4. Immune System Review (Kumaresan, 2016)"},"children":[{"data":{"text":"**Finding**: Systematically consolidates knowledge on the immune system of *M. rosenbergii* and summarizes immunoenhancement strategies."},"children":[]},{"data":{"text":"**Evaluation**: Integrates scattered research and offers clear practical guidance."},"children":[]}]}]},{"data":{"text":"III. Food Safety & Detection Technology"},"children":[{"data":{"text":"1. Enzymology & Preservation (Sriket, 2012)"},"children":[{"data":{"text":"**Finding**: First report of a low molecular weight (17 kDa) trypsin from the hepatopancreas of *M. rosenbergii* in crustaceans."},"children":[]},{"data":{"text":"**Evaluation**: Provides key evidence for understanding spoilage mechanisms at the molecular level, laying a foundation for preservation techniques."},"children":[]}]},{"data":{"text":"2. Drug Residue Detection (Van Poucke et al., 2011)"},"children":[{"data":{"text":"**Finding**: Semicarbazide (SEM) is not a reliable marker for nitrofurazone misuse; alternative detection methods are needed."},"children":[]},{"data":{"text":"**Evaluation**: Highlights the limitations of SEM as a marker and promotes refinement of related detection standards."},"children":[]}]}]},{"data":{"text":"IV. Environmental Stress & Biomarkers"},"children":[{"data":{"text":"1. Heavy Metal Response & MT Gene Expression (Mahmood et al., 2009)"},"children":[{"data":{"text":"**Finding**: The metallothionein gene Mar-MT-1 shows distinct expression patterns under exposure to Cd, Cu, Zn, and thermal stress."},"children":[]},{"data":{"text":"**Evaluation**: Systematically reveals MT gene regulation characteristics, holding significant reference value for heavy metal biomonitoring."},"children":[]}]}]},{"data":{"text":"V. Genetic Resources & Breeding Tools"},"children":[{"data":{"text":"1. Microsatellite Marker Development (Divu et al., 2008)"},"children":[{"data":{"text":"**Finding**: Isolated and characterized eight polymorphic microsatellite markers from *M. rosenbergii* via a microsatellite-enriched library."},"children":[]},{"data":{"text":"**Evaluation**: Systematically established a development and validation pipeline, filling the gap in high-throughput genetic markers for this species."},"children":[]}]}]},{"data":{"text":"VI. Research Trends & Future Directions","note":"#### Shift from single-factor to multi-stress and combined替换pollution studies.\n#### Increased integration of molecular, structural, and computational biology.\n#### Focus on species-specific mechanisms and practical, sustainable solutions.\n#### Need for cross-regional, cross-model validation of findings.\n#### Development of novel biomarkers and high-throughput genetic tools."},"children":[]}]},"template":"right","theme":"fresh-blue-compat","version":"1.4.43"}